result.execSummary:
The defendant Alyssa Lynne Baumeister was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Alyssa Lynne Baumeister in court.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.

Defendant Alyssa Lynne Baumeister in court with attorney J. Dennis Thornton.  Benjamin Calvin Verhulst appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction, with credit for 3 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 1 YEAR.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 10 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-A course in anger management.
-Maintain absolute sobriety.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim Michael M. unless approved by court or agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, surcharges, and restitution during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Any bail on deposit to apply.
-Restitution in the amount of $150.00 to Michael M.
-Provide DNA Sample.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
*Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a crime of domestic violence.

*Court grants expungement if all terms and conditions of sentence are completed. 

Filed:

Defendant Alyssa Lynne Baumeister in court with attorney J. Dennis Thornton.  Dax Odom appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT #2, dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.

AS TO COUNT #1: Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.  Parties are advised that EFFECTIVE August 3, 2015, this case will be assigned to JUDGE WAGNER, BRANCH 38, in Room 504 in the Courthouse.  Case adjourned for Sentencing Hearing in Branch 38 on 8-14-2015 at 8:15 am.  All conditions of bail are continued, including no contact Michael M., no weapons in possession and no violations of the law, until further order of the Court.   mld
